            "type": "text",
            "text": " function catches "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "max_tokens",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " truncation before any other loop logic. An "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ErrorLog",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " tracks consecutive failures for escalation and provides a diagnostic summary when the loop stops. API-level failures are handled with typed exception catches and exponential backoff. Together these layers ensure that no failure goes unclassified and the loop always terminates with a meaningful reason rather than crashing silently."
